3. Responsibilities
--------------------

3.1. Distribution of Source Form

All distribution of Covered Software in Source Code Form, including any
Modifications that You create or to which You contribute, must be under
the terms of this License. You must inform recipients of the Source Code
Form of the terms of this License by attaching Exhibit A.

You may not attempt to alter or restrict the recipients' rights in the
Source Code Form.

3.2. Distribution of Executable Form

If You distribute Covered Software in Executable Form then:

(a) such Covered Software must also be made available in Source Code Form,
    and You must inform recipients of the Executable Form how they can
    obtain a copy of such Source Code Form by the means described in
    Section 3.2(b); and

(b) You may distribute such Executable Form under the terms of this
    License, or under the terms of a Secondary License, if permitted under
    the terms of Section 3.3, provided that:

    (i) the conditions of Section 3.2(a) are met; and

    (ii) You include a notice containing the terms of Section 3.3 in a
         location where a recipient of the Executable Form can reasonably
         be expected to look for such a notice.

3.3. Distribution of a Larger Work

You may create and distribute a Larger Work under the terms of this
License or under the terms of one or more Secondary Licenses, provided
that:

(a) the terms of this License will continue to apply to the part of the
    Covered Software not Modified by You under the terms of the Secondary
    License; and

(b) a copy of this License and any Secondary Licenses applicable to such
    Covered Software and the Larger Work in their entirety and in an
    appropriate form be visibly displayed, or be made readily available
    upon request, in any documentation for such Larger Work where you
    describe recipients' rights relating to the Covered Software.

If it is impossible to put the text of such notice in a particular file
due to its structure, then You may include the notice in a location (such
as a relevant directory) where a recipient would be most likely to look
for such a notice.

If You created one or more Modification(s) You may add your name as a
Contributor to the notice described in Exhibit A of any Covered Software
that You distribute. If it would be useful to clearly identify the
ownership of the Contribution, add the following line within such notice:

    "Portions created by [name] are Copyright [year] [name]. All Rights
    Reserved."

3.4. Notices

You may not remove or alter the substance of any license notices
(including copyright notices, patent notices, disclaimers of warranty, or
